id: pm-uwfs
title: "Context usage feedback signal: served-then-acted-on outcomes strengthen relevance scoring (retrieval-practice effect)"
description: "Close the loop between context assembly and what agents actually did with it: derive a bounded usage signal (items served by context/next that the same author subsequently read, claimed, mutated, or closed) and feed it back into the pm-4k6b scorer as a strengthening/calibration input, mirroring how human recall strengthens memory traces."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 3
tags[4]: cognitive-memory,context,relevance,sdk-first
created_at: "2026-07-07T06:50:19.358Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-12T19:07:34.334Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 600
acceptance_criteria: "A derived, append-only usage ledger records (serving, author, served ids, subsequent touch within a horizon) with bounded size and a documented retention/compaction policy; the ledger is derived data — never mutates tracked items and is excluded from item history-chain integrity; pm-4k6b scorer accepts a usage-affinity signal with a documented default weight and per-signal explanation in the score breakdown; signal is workspace-local, contains no content beyond item ids/timestamps/author, and can be disabled via config with zero residual cost; pm-atfm harness gains implicit-judgment scenarios (served-and-used vs served-and-ignored) to validate the signal improves ranking rather than entrenching it; popularity-bias guard: a documented exploration/decay term prevents self-reinforcing lock-in of already-surfaced items; no daemon (ADR pm-i7i4) — capture happens inline on the commands that already run"
parent: pm-4k6b
risk: medium
confidence: low
